T. 9.0 ; wt 335.8 g,  Typology:,  Faces appear to have been virt. flat in cross section - sides slightly bowed poss with tendency to double facetting - but no crisp bevel extant ; intact body angles fairly crisp with minimal lipping in evidence; certainly no central bevel; despite loss of sur. but had evid. been pretty thin.,  Manufacture:,  Evid. for moderately set e. bev. - crest of bevel just perceptible in spots; some monor asymmetry in provilfe - but slightly flattter face is more curved close to butt than is reverse.  ,  Condition:,  No indication of dam. prior to corrosion etc. ; score/rub marks down either butt side & file ripples across either butt side, all assoc. with gold flecking - modern interference by finder and his colleagues ; none of c.e. intact,  Attached material:,  v. little trace of yellow soil, in one case forming accretion like spot with admixture of white grains (calcium?)
